                    "paragraphOrdinal": 1,
                    "paragraphTitle": "Question forms",
                    "paragraphSubtitles": [
                        "Indirect questions"
                    ],
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "We use indirect questions when we want to be more polite."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 2,
                    "paragraphTitle": null,
                    "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "They usually start with phrases like Could you tell me...?, Do you know...? and Would you mind...?"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 3,
                    "paragraphTitle": null,
                    "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "In indirect questions we use the same word order as a statement (i.e. subject + verb) and we don't use the auxiliary do."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 4,
                    "paragraphTitle": null,
                    "paragraphSubtitles": [
                        "Questions with prepositions"
                    ],
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "If a verb is followed by a preposition, the preposition comes at the end of the sentence."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 5,
                    "paragraphTitle": null,
                    "paragraphSubtitles": [
                        "Subject questions"
                    ],
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "When we ask about the subject of a sentence, we use the same word order as a statement, and the question word (e.g. when, who, what, which, etc) replaces the subject."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "paragraphOrdinal": 6,
                    "paragraphTitle": null,
                    "paragraphSubtitles": [
                        "Negative questions"
                    ],
                    "paragraphContents": [
                        "When we ask negative wh- questions, we use the auxiliary verb, even in subject questions."
                    ]
                }
            ],
